Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) comprising nickel + iron anode support and gadolinia-cloped ceria (GDC) of composition Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta thin film electrolyte were fabricated, and their performance was evaluated.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The ratio of Fe2O3 to NiO in the anode support was 3 to 7 on a molar basis.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: Fe2O3 and NiO powders were mixed in the desired proportions and discs were die-pressed.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: All other layers were sequentially applied on the anode support.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell structure consisted of five distinct layers: anode support - Ni + Fe; anode functional layer - Ni + CDC; electrolyte - CDC; cathode functional layer - LSC (La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta) +
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: CDC; and cathode current collector - LSC.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: Cells with three different variations of the electrolyte were made: (1) thin CDC electrolyte (similar to 15 mu m); (2) thick CDC electrolyte (similar to 25 mu m); and (3) trilayer GDC/thin yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ)/GDC electrolyte (similar to 25 mu m).
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: Cells were tested with hydrogen as fuel and air as oxidant up to 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The maximum open circuit voltage measured at 650 degrees C was similar to 0.83 V and maximum power density measured was similar to 0.68 Wcm(-2).
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte

Sentencas: The present work shows that cells with Fe + Ni containing anode support can be Successfully made.
Titulo: Bimetallic (Ni-Fe) anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells with gadolinia-doped ceria electrolyte
